This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for automated hyperparameter optimization using gradient descent, which is a fundamental technique in machine learning. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these fields heavily rely on machine learning techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of gradient-based optimization in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), which are also likely sub-categories.
